The African National Congress (ANC) in Mpumalanga has suspended its deputy convener of the Ehlanzeni region, Michael Ngwenya, for mobilising party branches in the province and going to Nkandla in northern KwaZulu-Natal to support former President Jacob Zuma.   Ngwenya, who is the former Chairperson of the Ehlanzeni region, is the second person to be suspended from the party in less than a week.  Video: Activities outside Zuma’s home in Nkandla as his arrest is imminent: Simphiwe Makhanya Video: Jacob Zuma’s address speech to his supporters in Nkandla, KwaZulu-Natal   Earlier this week Umkhonto we Sizwe Military Veterans’ Association Spokesperson Carl Niehaus was suspended from the ANC for allegedly bringing the party into disrepute. He has vowed to appeal against the suspension. Video: ANC briefs media on suspension of Carl Niehaus   